	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Both DKL3 and the japanese color version have copy protection of sorts. Basically there is a loop that writes to registers used in flash cart mappers to screw up the settings and crash the game. To prevent this you just remove the actual write to register.
<br />
<br />In Donkey Kong Land 3 (U) its at $F5F2. In the japanese color version it's at $F5FB. The original sequence of code is: 02031D20FAAFEA0000C9. You want to change it to: <strong>00</strong>031D20FAAFEA0000C9. The game should run now.
<br />
<br />Oh yes and don't forget to fix the checksum.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


